rComments: Excellent teacher. I would take his class again.

Jean-Laurent is very knowledgeable and clearly very passionate about mental health nursing. I found him very engaging and was almost always interested in the content. He has 2 midterms (20% each), one paper (20%), and a final (40%). I found the first midterm and the final to me more focused on the textbook while the second midterm from his slides.
Insightful and experienced in his field. Considerate of his students. Hard test questions.

Prof. Domingue is very smart with lots of experience. One word to describe him is FAIR. Gives a lot of feedback and is always available to review things with you. Explanations for mark deductions very often made sense (room for improvement). Could be more clear with where marks come from on midterms, but he did a great job with virtual learning.
